# Documentation Maintenance Rules

## Always Keep Updated
- **OpenAPI documentation** must be updated when adding new endpoints
- **Postman collection** must be updated when adding new requests
- **Cursor rules** must be updated when project structure changes
- **Cursor commands** must be updated when workflows change

## Documentation Standards
- Use proper file references: [filename](mdc:path)
- Include comprehensive examples
- Test all examples before committing
- Validate syntax of all documentation files

## Update Triggers
- New API endpoints added
- Authentication changes
- New validation rules
- Project structure changes
- Technology stack updates

## Key Files to Maintain
- [src/main/resources/openapi/documentation.yaml](mdc:src/main/resources/openapi/documentation.yaml) - OpenAPI/Swagger docs
- [postman_collection.json](mdc:postman_collection.json) - Postman collection
- [.cursor/rules/](mdc:.cursor/rules) - Cursor rules directory
- [.cursor/commands/](mdc:.cursor/commands/) - Cursor commands directory
- [.cursor/instructions/](mdc:.cursor/instructions/) - Cursor instructions directory
- [README.md](mdc:README.md) - Project documentation

## Validation Commands
```bash
# Validate OpenAPI YAML
python -c "import yaml; yaml.safe_load(open('src/main/resources/openapi/documentation.yaml'))"

# Validate Postman JSON
python -c "import json; json.load(open('postman_collection.json'))"

# Check file references in rules
grep -r "mdc:" .cursor/rules/
```